    "These terms appear only in the energy and magnetic field equations, so Eq. 54 is written as",
    "where the vector w corresponds to either w = [B 1, e tot ](r, t) or w = [B 1, e int ](r, t).",
    "The components of the operator S(w) are defined as,",
    "For the STS scheme the stability is imposed at the end of a bigger step called a superstep, t STS.",
    "The t STS is calculated as a sum of substeps τ j, obtained using the modified Chebyshev polynomials (Alexiades, Amiez, and Gremaud, 1996)."
